subject: Re: Llan, Loch, Ax and Exam
msgSnippet: Strange, I remember seeing those when I still used the substitution fonts. If your setup allows it, I personally would recommend using the placeholder Unicode
messageBody:
Strange, I remember seeing those when I still used the substitution fonts. If your setup allows it, I personally would recommend using the placeholder Unicode fonts for writing in Quickscript. It makes mixing Orthodox and QS a lot easier and is really nice if you want to keep your digital QS writings around.

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "cossyrosario" <cossyrosario@...> wrote:
>
> These are four characters present in the Wikipedia Chart
> <http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b6/Quickscript_alphabet\
> _revised_names.png> which I do not find in the Junior Script font. And
> apparently not in the King Script font either.
>
> I also don't find Eat, Age and Ash in the Junior Script font.
>
> What font, if any, contains them?
>
